#26710
{BOL}{GRE}Down Below{gre}~
The heat comes from the heat exchangers and processors which feed down
from the boulevards on the upper levels. The light comes from whatever
bulbs can be scrounged from topside. Occasionally starlight rises in
narrow beams through portholes set in the floor. Once every twenty-four
hours Epsilon Eridani shines through the portholes, but that light is
diffused by distance and by grime on the crystal alloy panes. Even so it
lights up Down Below in a series of radiating shafts, each moving as
the station rotates, to send ovals of light gliding slowly across the
walls, ceilings, the people, the machinery, the service ducts and stalls.
~
